  "chapter": {
    "number": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Anger against Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2503
          },
          {
            "text": "spoke, there was trembling;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he was exalted in Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But he incurred guilt through Baal,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he died.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now they sin more and more",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and make for themselves cast images,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "idols skillfully made from their silver,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all of them the work of craftsmen.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "People say of them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“They offer human sacrifice",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and kiss the calves!”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2504
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore they will be like the morning mist,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like the early dew that vanishes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like chaff blown from a threshing floor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like smoke through an open window.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet I am the LORD your God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "ever since the land of Egypt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you know no God but Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for there is no Savior besides Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I knew you in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the land of drought.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When they had pasture,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they became satisfied;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when they were satisfied,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their hearts became proud,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and as a result they forgot Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So like a lion I will pounce on them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a leopard I will lurk by the path.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a bear robbed of her cubs I will attack them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will tear open their chests.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "There I will devour them like a lion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a wild beast would tear them apart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Death and Resurrection"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You are destroyed, O Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because you are against Me—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "against your helper.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where is your king now",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2505
          },
          {
            "text": "to save you in all your cities,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the rulers to whom you said,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Give me a king and princes”?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So in My anger I gave you a king,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in My wrath I took him away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The iniquity of Ephraim is bound up;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his sin is stored up.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Labor pains come upon him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he is an unwise son.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When the time arrives,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he fails to present himself at the opening of the womb.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will ransom them from the power of Sheol;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will redeem them from Death.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2506
          },
          {
            "text": "Where, O Death, are your plagues?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Where, O Sheol, is your sting?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2507
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Compassion is hidden from My eyes.",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment on Samaria"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Although he flourishes among his brothers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "an east wind will come—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a wind from the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rising up from the desert.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "His fountain will fail,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his spring will run dry.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The wind will plunder his treasury",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of every precious article.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Samaria will bear her guilt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because she has rebelled against her God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will fall by the sword;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their little ones will be dashed to pieces,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and their pregnant women ripped open.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
